---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
<main>
  <h1>🧑‍💻 Hey, it's Humza</h1>
  <p>
    Welcome to the corner of the internet run by <strong>Humza Arshed Javaid</strong> — Maryland native, cloud architect, and occasional roti enthusiast. (Yes, that's where "Roti Mason" comes from: a bit more than curry.)
  </p>
  <p>
    Grew up in the Leonardtown / Mechanicsville area, studied at UMBC (University of Maryland Baltimore County), and cut my teeth in cloud solutions and emerging tech — including time at Smartronix (now part of SMX) building systems that actually matter.
  </p>
  <p>
    These days I'm at <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/humzajavaid">ElasticBin</a> as a Founding Architect, tinkering with scalable infrastructure and keeping things running smoothly. When I'm not in the cloud, I'm back home, posting low-key takes on X (@humzinator), moving furniture, or reminding myself why family ties run deep (shoutout to my dad, Arshed Javaid — engineer, Parraid co-founder, and all-around legend).
  </p>
  <p>Quick ways to poke around here:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Scroll my latest thoughts on <a href="https://x.com/humzinator">X</a> — mostly casual, sometimes spicy</li>
    <li>Check my LinkedIn for the professional timeline</li>
    <li>Hit me up if you're into cloud architecture, South Asian food debates, or just vibes</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Keep it real. If you're building something cool or just passing through, say hi. 🚀
  </p>
  <h1>🧑‍💻 About Me</h1>

  <p>
    Hey, I'm Humza Arshed Javaid — Maryland native (Leonardtown/Mechanicsville area), cloud architect, and Founding Architect at <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/humzajavaid">ElasticBin</a>. I design scalable infrastructure and mission-critical systems, mostly on AWS.
  </p>

  <p>
    Systems Engineering from UMBC. Before ElasticBin, I spent years at SMX (formerly Smartronix) building cloud solutions. Engineering is in the family — my dad, Arshed Javaid, co-founded Parraid after decades in telemetry and reliable systems.
  </p>

  <p>
    Certified: <strong>AWS Certified DevOps Engineer – Professional</strong> (2022) and <strong>AWS Certified Machine Learning – Specialty</strong> (2023). Heavy Terraform user for declarative IaC — provisioning, modules, state management, brownfield imports, and keeping environments reproducible and drift-free.
  </p>

  <p>
    Off the clock: back home, posting casual/spicy takes as <a href="https://x.com/humzinator">@humzinator</a> (Roti Mason: a bit more than curry), debating South Asian food, or just keeping it real. No hype, steady progress.
  </p>

  <p>
    Cloud infra, Terraform workflows, ML on AWS, roti recipes, or good vibes? Say hi on X or LinkedIn. 🚀
  </p>
</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
